RKE2 Air-Gap Installation on Ubuntu Using Ansible (Single Node)
1. Overview
This document describes the process of deploying RKE2 Kubernetes in an air-gapped environment using Ansible automation on Ubuntu.
Air-gap installations are used in environments where servers do not have internet access, such as secure enterprise networks, government infrastructure, or banking systems.
In this setup:
RKE2 artifacts are downloaded on an internet-enabled machine.


Files are transferred to the target node using Ansible.


Kubernetes is installed and configured automatically.



