8. Ansible Playbook
The deployment is automated using deploy.yml.
This playbook performs the following tasks:
Disable system swap


Install required packages


Create RKE2 directories


Copy air-gap artifacts


Install RKE2 using local files


Start RKE2 server


Configure kubectl


Verify Kubernetes cluster



9. Run the Deployment
Execute the playbook from the Ansible machine:
ansible-playbook -i inventory.ini deploy.yml --ask-pass --ask-become-pass
During execution:
Ansible connects to the target node via SSH


Copies RKE2 artifacts


Installs RKE2


Starts the Kubernetes cluster



10. RKE2 Installation Process
During the deployment the following operations occur.
Disable Swap
Swap must be disabled for Kubernetes to work properly.
swapoff -a

Install Dependencies
Required packages:
curl
tar

Create Required Directories
/etc/rancher/rke2
/var/lib/rancher/rke2/agent/images
These directories store configuration and container images.

Copy Air-Gap Files
Ansible copies the artifact directory to the target node:
/tmp/rke2-airgap

Move Container Images
The image archive is placed in:
/var/lib/rancher/rke2/agent/images/
RKE2 automatically loads these images during startup.

Install RKE2
Installation uses the local artifact path:
INSTALL_RKE2_ARTIFACT_PATH=/tmp/rke2-airgap sh /tmp/rke2-airgap/install.sh

11. Start RKE2 Server
After installation the service is enabled and started.
systemctl enable rke2-server
systemctl start rke2-server
Check service status:
sudo systemctl status rke2-server
Expected output:
Active: active (running)

12. Configure kubectl
Create Kubernetes config directory:
/home/ubuntu/.kube
Copy kubeconfig file:
/etc/rancher/rke2/rke2.yaml
Set environment variable:
export KUBECONFIG=/home/ubuntu/.kube/config
This allows the ubuntu user to run kubectl commands without sudo.

13. Verify Kubernetes Cluster
Check cluster nodes:
kubectl get nodes
Example output:
NAME            STATUS   ROLES
ubuntu-vm-1     Ready    control-plane,etcd,master

Check system pods:
kubectl get pods -A
Common system components include:
kube-system
├── coredns
├── canal
├── metrics-server
└── ingress-nginx

14. Cluster Verification Commands
Common commands used to verify cluster health:
kubectl get nodes
kubectl get pods -A
kubectl cluster-info
kubectl get svc -A
Check RKE2 logs:
sudo journalctl -u rke2-server -f

15. Result
After successful deployment:
A single-node Kubernetes cluster is running.


RKE2 manages the Kubernetes control plane.


Container runtime containerd is installed automatically.


kubectl is configured for the ubuntu user.


Core Kubernetes system pods are running.


Deploy.yml



---
- hosts: rke2
  become: yes

  tasks:

  - name: Disable swap
    command: swapoff -a

  - name: Install dependencies
    apt:
      name:
        - curl
        - tar
      state: present
      update_cache: yes

  - name: Create required directories
    file:
      path: "{{ item }}"
      state: directory
      mode: '0755'
    loop:
      - /etc/rancher/rke2
      - /var/lib/rancher/rke2/agent/images

  - name: Copy airgap files
    copy:
      src: files/rke2-airgap/
      dest: /tmp/rke2-airgap/
      mode: '0755'

  - name: Move airgap images
    command: cp /tmp/rke2-airgap/rke2-images.linux-amd64.tar.zst /var/lib/rancher/rke2/agent/images/

  - name: Install RKE2
    shell: INSTALL_RKE2_ARTIFACT_PATH=/tmp/rke2-airgap sh /tmp/rke2-airgap/install.sh

  - name: Enable and start RKE2
    systemd:
      name: rke2-server
      enabled: yes
      state: started

  - name: Create kubectl symlink
    file:
      src: /var/lib/rancher/rke2/bin/kubectl
      dest: /usr/local/bin/kubectl
      state: link

  - name: Wait for kubeconfig to be created
    wait_for:
      path: /etc/rancher/rke2/rke2.yaml
      timeout: 300

  - name: Wait for Kubernetes API server
    wait_for:
      port: 6443
      delay: 10
      timeout: 300

  - name: Create .kube directory for ubuntu
    file:
      path: /home/ubuntu/.kube
      state: directory
      owner: ubuntu
      group: ubuntu
      mode: '0755'

  - name: Copy kubeconfig for ubuntu user
    copy:
      src: /etc/rancher/rke2/rke2.yaml
      dest: /home/ubuntu/.kube/config
      remote_src: yes
      owner: ubuntu
      group: ubuntu
      mode: '0600'

  - name: Set KUBECONFIG in ubuntu bashrc
    lineinfile:
      path: /home/ubuntu/.bashrc
      line: export KUBECONFIG=/home/ubuntu/.kube/config
      create: yes

  - name: Verify cluster
    command: kubectl get nodes
    environment:
      KUBECONFIG: /home/ubuntu/.kube/config


